# Environment Variables

## Database
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/skaitomanas

## JWT
JWT_SECRET=your-super-secret-jwt-key-change-this-in-production
JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=your-super-secret-refresh-key-change-this-in-production

## Server
PORT=3000
NODE_ENV=development

## File Upload Configuration
# Directory where uploaded files will be stored (relative to backend root)
# Default: public/uploads
UPLOAD_DIR=public/uploads

# Maximum file size in bytes
# Default: 5242880 (5MB)
# Examples:
#   1MB = 1048576
#   5MB = 5242880
#   10MB = 10485760
MAX_FILE_SIZE=5242880

## Deployment Notes
# For production deployment:
# 1. Copy this file to .env in production
# 2. Change JWT secrets to strong random values:
#    node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
# 3. Set NODE_ENV=production
# 4. Update DATABASE_URL with production credentials
# 5. Ensure UPLOAD_DIR exists and has write permissions (755)
# 6. Set up regular backups of the upload directory
# 7. See PRODUCTION_SETUP.md for complete deployment guide

